14
00:00:46.805 --> 00:00:48.048
Yeah?

15
00:00:49.635 --> 00:00:50.671
No.

16
00:00:53.122 --> 00:00:54.847
No. she won't.

17
00:00:54.882 --> 00:00:57.505
Because you're gonna
make sure she never finds out.

18
00:00:57.540 --> 00:00:59.921
You took us there!

19
00:00:59.956 --> 00:01:02.096
What you know about them.
you can't just walk away.

20
00:01:02.131 --> 00:01:04.512
It's done. Ed.
It's over to you now.

21
00:01:04.547 --> 00:01:06.652
Alexander runs the money.

22
00:01:06.687 --> 00:01:08.723
Let Sean build his buildings.

23
00:01:08.758 --> 00:01:11.174
I'm giving you everything. Ed

24
00:01:11.209 --> 00:01:14.074
and all you have to do
is keep this to yourself.

25
00:01:15.454 --> 00:01:17.180
That's all you have to do.

26
00:01:32.540 --> 00:01:33.403
Finn!

27
00:01:34.956 --> 00:01:36.751
You can't just walk away!

28
00:01:36.786 --> 00:01:39.271
It's all yours now. Ed.

29
00:01:39.306 --> 00:01:41.687
We met as young teenagers

30
00:01:41.722 --> 00:01:43.517
on the streets of London.

31
00:01:43.551 --> 00:01:45.691
A city of closed doors.

32
00:01:46.520 --> 00:01:47.693
By the time we were done...

33
00:01:48.867 --> 00:01:52.664
there would not be
one single door

34
00:01:52.698 --> 00:01:55.701
in this city that we could not
get behind.

35
00:01:55.736 --> 00:01:59.843
He led. I followed.

36
00:01:59.878 --> 00:02:03.709
And I am so proud to have worked
for the man all these years.

37
00:02:04.952 --> 00:02:09.784
I dedicate my heart
and soul to you.

38
00:04:08.075 --> 00:04:10.077
Hello. this is Dave's Mechanics

39
00:04:10.111 --> 00:04:11.837
Please leave a message
after the beep

40
00:04:11.872 --> 00:04:13.701
and we'll get back to you.

41
00:04:13.736 --> 00:04:15.600
Vic. yeah. it's me. Listen.

42
00:04:16.980 --> 00:04:18.948
I'm looking at a lot of faces
on my wall

43
00:04:18.982 --> 00:04:20.708
and something is missing.

44
00:04:20.743 --> 00:04:22.020
Someone is missing.

45
00:04:24.022 --> 00:04:25.782
There's someone else
above all this.

46
00:05:09.723 --> 00:05:11.828
You need to get
these shipments moving.

47
00:05:12.795 --> 00:05:14.175
I'm with him.

48
00:05:14.210 --> 00:05:15.936
I don't want any more hold-ups.
OK.

49
00:05:15.970 --> 00:05:16.902
Let's go faster.
OK.

50
00:05:24.151 --> 00:05:25.911
Go!

51
00:05:47.692 --> 00:05:48.486
Mm-hm.

52
00:06:41.780 --> 00:06:43.161
Does Luan know?

53
00:06:43.195 --> 00:06:44.714
No. he's unaware the transfer

54
00:06:44.749 --> 00:06:46.026
didn't go through
last night.

55
00:06:46.060 --> 00:06:47.165
How long have we got?

56
00:06:47.199 --> 00:06:48.718
We don't need a war
with the Albanians.

57
00:06:49.616 --> 00:06:51.790
Not long.

58
00:06:51.825 --> 00:06:54.034
Luan's in business
with Uche Mossanya.

59
00:06:54.068 --> 00:06:55.415
Uche Mossanya?

60
00:06:55.829 --> 00:06:57.002
"Mosi".

61
00:06:57.934 --> 00:06:59.591
Nigerian gangster. nasty.

62
00:07:00.178 --> 00:07:02.007
The money's owed to him.

63
00:07:02.042 --> 00:07:04.907
Luan's the only person standing
between us at the moment.

64
00:07:04.941 --> 00:07:06.633
Who the fuck did this?

65
00:07:06.667 --> 00:07:09.290
Who got into our accounts
and stole half a billion?

66
00:07:09.325 --> 00:07:12.017
I'm working on it.
We'll find it.

67
00:07:12.052 --> 00:07:13.087
Where are you?

68
00:07:16.332 --> 00:07:19.715
I'm at the Belvedere Tower
watching the contractors

69
00:07:19.749 --> 00:07:20.992
sign off on the new build.

70
00:07:22.131 --> 00:07:23.719
It's looking very impressive.
Sean

71
00:07:23.753 --> 00:07:25.030
I think you're going to be
very happy with it.

72
00:07:26.273 --> 00:07:28.206
We need to stick closer
than ever

73
00:07:28.240 --> 00:07:29.518
if we want to survive this.

74
00:07:31.658 --> 00:07:33.073
You know you don't need
to say that. Sean.

75
00:07:33.107 --> 00:07:35.178
Don't I?

76
00:07:35.213 --> 00:07:38.250
You're not always there
when someone takes a shot at me.

77
00:07:48.019 --> 00:07:49.296
He knows I'm lying.

78
00:07:51.229 --> 00:07:52.644
We can't keep this up.

79
00:07:52.679 --> 00:07:53.956
We should've just told him
in the beginning.

80
00:07:53.990 --> 00:07:56.027
Told him what. Alex?

81
00:07:56.061 --> 00:07:57.822
That his father didn't believe
in him enough

82
00:07:57.856 --> 00:07:59.202
to trust him with the business?

83
00:07:59.237 --> 00:08:01.619
That he wanted you
to run it instead?

84
00:08:01.653 --> 00:08:04.173
That he was gonna run off
and leave his family?

85
00:08:04.207 --> 00:08:07.728
And all while Sean was preparing
his father's grave.

86
00:08:07.763 --> 00:08:10.006
Or should I have told him even
our investors want him dead

87
00:08:10.041 --> 00:08:11.525
and you in charge?

88
00:08:11.560 --> 00:08:12.940
I was protecting him.

89
00:08:12.975 --> 00:08:14.183
Fucking Finn.

90
00:08:14.217 --> 00:08:15.253
What if it's worse?

91
00:08:15.771 --> 00:08:17.255
Worse?

92
00:08:17.289 --> 00:08:18.567
You didn't know
about Finn's deal

93
00:08:18.601 --> 00:08:20.051
with Luan
and the Albanian family.

94
00:08:20.085 --> 00:08:21.846
What else do you think Finn
hadn't told you?

95
00:08:24.055 --> 00:08:25.332
Must've crossed your mind.

96
00:08:26.575 --> 00:08:28.715
He had both the access
and the knowledge

97
00:08:28.749 --> 00:08:29.578
to take that money.

98
00:08:30.924 --> 00:08:32.891
He's dead. Alex.

99
00:08:32.926 --> 00:08:35.066
Doesn't mean he hadn't already
set the wheels in motion.

100
00:08:36.412 --> 00:08:37.551
Then that would mean...

101
00:08:40.865 --> 00:08:42.107
he fucked us all.

102
00:12:34.857 --> 00:12:35.893
Hekar...

103
00:12:36.307 --> 00:12:37.204
Hekar!

104
00:14:08.433 --> 00:14:10.435
The place belonged
to a Tove Frandsen.

105
00:14:10.470 --> 00:14:12.058
Mercenary from Denmark.

106
00:14:12.472 --> 00:14:14.508
Special Forces.

107
00:14:14.543 --> 00:14:16.338
When you raid the place.
you'll find a weapons cache

108
00:14:16.372 --> 00:14:19.203
next to her kids' toys.

109
00:14:19.237 --> 00:14:21.412
The licensed taxi you were
looking for is registered

110
00:14:21.446 --> 00:14:23.966
to a Leif Hansen
at a different address.

111
00:14:25.174 --> 00:14:26.279
OK...

112
00:14:27.349 --> 00:14:28.453
Anything else?

113
00:14:42.088 --> 00:14:43.399
Why don't you look surprised?

114
00:14:45.194 --> 00:14:47.058
Someone broke into my flat
a week ago...

115
00:14:49.129 --> 00:14:51.476
took a boxcutter to my mouth

116
00:14:51.511 --> 00:14:53.513
in my sleep.
and sent me the video.

117
00:14:56.723 --> 00:14:58.345
They're trying to warn me off
Floriana.

118
00:15:00.658 --> 00:15:01.970
Why didn't you tell me?

119
00:15:05.525 --> 00:15:06.975
Finn's murder inquiry's
been shut down.

120
00:15:10.012 --> 00:15:11.289
I don't know who to trust.

121
00:15:16.777 --> 00:15:17.951
You can trust me.

122
00:15:24.509 --> 00:15:26.201
Armed Police!

123
00:15:26.235 --> 00:15:28.306
We've entered
the property at location one.

124
00:15:28.341 --> 00:15:29.583
Arriving at second location.

125
00:15:29.618 --> 00:15:32.241
Armed police!

126
00:15:32.276 --> 00:15:33.656
Entering property two.

127
00:15:38.661 --> 00:15:39.731
Clear!

128
00:15:39.766 --> 00:15:40.732
Property one. clear.

129
00:15:42.596 --> 00:15:44.529
Starting search
and sweep of property two.

130
00:15:59.475 --> 00:16:01.167
...all clear
in property one. over.

131
00:16:09.623 --> 00:16:10.590
All clear. ma'am.

132
00:16:14.387 --> 00:16:15.284
Yep...

133
00:16:18.287 --> 00:16:19.668
Just a few animals. really.

134
00:16:20.600 --> 00:16:21.670
Yeah...

135
00:16:22.705 --> 00:16:23.810
Yeah. yeah.

136
00:16:25.398 --> 00:16:26.468
Yeah. Yep.

137
00:16:27.434 --> 00:16:28.573
DI Chung.

138
00:16:29.747 --> 00:16:32.198
Interesting place.
You live here?

139
00:16:32.232 --> 00:16:34.579
Yes. I'm a retired nurse.

140
00:16:34.614 --> 00:16:36.616
Anyone else?
My son.

141
00:16:39.377 --> 00:16:40.620
Where is he?

142
00:16:40.654 --> 00:16:43.588
At work. He's an engineer.

143
00:17:30.532 --> 00:17:31.464
Find Lale.

144
00:18:32.594 --> 00:18:33.974
You find anything?

145
00:18:34.009 --> 00:18:35.217
She's not there.

146
00:18:36.356 --> 00:18:37.599
Let's scrub this down!

147
00:18:37.633 --> 00:18:38.841
Everything.

148
00:18:38.876 --> 00:18:40.153
Yes. boss.

149
00:18:40.188 --> 00:18:40.981
This never happened.

150
00:18:43.018 --> 00:18:45.572
This is Asif.
it needs an answer.

151
00:18:45.607 --> 00:18:47.505
Yeah. Yeah. it does.

152
00:18:48.472 --> 00:18:49.680
Let me in on it.

153
00:18:49.714 --> 00:18:50.991
Sorting things out. I can help.

154
00:18:51.026 --> 00:18:52.200
Yeah. good.

155
00:18:53.925 --> 00:18:55.444
Right. keep looking.

156
00:18:55.479 --> 00:18:57.205
This is Asif. has to be.

157
00:18:57.239 --> 00:18:58.792
And we need to make good
with him.

158
00:18:59.931 --> 00:19:01.726
Asif attacking Lale
is an attack on us.

159
00:19:01.761 --> 00:19:03.418
No. It's an attack on Lale.

160
00:19:03.452 --> 00:19:04.971
You bet on the wrong dog. mate.

161
00:19:07.042 --> 00:19:09.009
Now is not the time
for further risks.

162
00:19:09.044 --> 00:19:10.839
You'll just be throwing petrol
on the fire

163
00:19:10.873 --> 00:19:12.496
one we can't control.

164
00:19:12.530 --> 00:19:14.291
How close are you to finding out
who stole the half a billion?

165
00:19:16.465 --> 00:19:17.915
He knows.

166
00:19:20.504 --> 00:19:21.574
Mosi's in London.

167
00:19:22.885 --> 00:19:24.093
Half of the money was his.

168
00:19:27.580 --> 00:19:29.961
He'll go after Luan
first but we should be ready.

169
00:19:31.446 --> 00:19:33.275
Take the legs. go on...

170
00:19:33.310 --> 00:19:35.035
Come on. man. let's go.

171
00:19:35.070 --> 00:19:37.555
OK. one. two. three...

172
00:19:45.080 --> 00:19:46.323
Gentlemen.

173
00:19:50.672 --> 00:19:52.329
My money is gone.

174
00:19:57.265 --> 00:19:58.956
The Wallaces. Luan Dushaj

175
00:19:58.990 --> 00:20:00.785
and the bankers have
stolen from me.

176
00:20:02.511 --> 00:20:03.823
They are all thieves.

177
00:21:43.405 --> 00:21:44.372
Go?
Mm.

178
00:22:04.530 --> 00:22:07.326
Zeus. Enough.

179
00:22:19.924 --> 00:22:21.029
There's no money here.

180
00:22:28.105 --> 00:22:30.210
We're not a bank!

181
00:22:30.245 --> 00:22:32.868
It's just numbers. you see?
Just numbers!

182
00:22:34.422 --> 00:22:35.940
No. no. no!

183
00:22:35.975 --> 00:22:37.114
Please! Please!

184
00:22:37.148 --> 00:22:38.184
Please. please. no!

185
00:22:41.187 --> 00:22:42.533
No. no!

186
00:22:51.715 --> 00:22:52.578
Dad!

187
00:22:53.648 --> 00:22:54.683
Dad!

188
00:22:56.167 --> 00:22:58.204
This is going to be chaos!

189
00:22:58.238 --> 00:23:00.827
Please. it's her birthday today.
For Mummy. behave.

190
00:23:02.484 --> 00:23:04.590
Oh. thank you so much!

191
00:23:05.867 --> 00:23:06.971
Thank you. thank you.
thank you.

192
00:23:08.110 --> 00:23:10.527
This girl will be spoiled
by all of this!

193
00:23:37.657 --> 00:23:38.727
Luan?
It'll be OK.

194
00:23:50.808 --> 00:23:52.534
Brought a gift
for the birthday girl.

195
00:23:54.502 --> 00:23:55.641
Something a little different.

196
00:23:56.607 --> 00:23:57.884
Good to see you. Mosi.

197
00:23:57.919 --> 00:23:58.851
What are you doing here?

198
00:24:00.266 --> 00:24:01.992
You thought it would work?

199
00:24:02.026 --> 00:24:03.614
Stealing from me.

200
00:24:03.649 --> 00:24:05.064
Everything is fine.
the money has gone through.

201
00:24:05.098 --> 00:24:07.515
Not my money. You took it.

202
00:24:08.792 --> 00:24:11.277
Mosi. please.
that's not possible!

203
00:24:11.311 --> 00:24:12.968
You caught us out.

204
00:24:13.003 --> 00:24:14.176
It was a mistake. then?

205
00:24:14.211 --> 00:24:16.213
That you stole from us. yes.

206
00:24:16.247 --> 00:24:17.870
No. no. no.
Our deal is off.

207
00:24:17.904 --> 00:24:19.181
We are being set up. man.

208
00:24:19.216 --> 00:24:21.045
Repay everything.

209
00:24:21.080 --> 00:24:22.702
Mosi. this has to be
the Wallaces--

210
00:24:22.737 --> 00:24:24.601
Or I butcher everyone
you hold precious.

211
00:24:26.188 --> 00:24:27.569
Every single one of them.

212
00:24:32.574 --> 00:24:34.196
What's her name?
My name's Bukoroshe.

213
00:24:34.231 --> 00:24:36.820
Ah. Such a pretty name...

214
00:24:37.752 --> 00:24:38.753
Bukoroshe.

215
00:24:40.237 --> 00:24:41.480
Bukoroshe.

216
00:24:50.730 --> 00:24:52.214
Oh. a puppy!

217
00:24:59.187 --> 00:25:00.844
I love him!

218
00:25:05.020 --> 00:25:06.332
You made a mistake. man.

219
00:25:07.851 --> 00:25:09.128
All of the money.

220
00:25:25.903 --> 00:25:27.560
...where 11 employees

221
00:25:27.595 --> 00:25:30.667
from the Adige investment
house have been found

222
00:25:30.701 --> 00:25:33.635
with their hands severed
at the wrist.

223
00:25:33.670 --> 00:25:36.051
In other news.
the controversial Belvedere tower

224
00:25:36.086 --> 00:25:37.639
will open today as planned--

225
00:26:21.821 --> 00:26:23.271
I think he's just
holding onto what happened...

226
00:26:26.792 --> 00:26:29.070
Cos you can't
afford it. that's why!

227
00:26:43.222 --> 00:26:44.844
You're a fucking liar. Ed.

228
00:26:45.983 --> 00:26:47.019
Where's my money?

229
00:26:48.123 --> 00:26:49.642
You said we had a deal.

230
00:26:51.851 --> 00:26:53.922
I have to kill a fucking family
for this.

231
00:26:53.957 --> 00:26:54.889
You understand?

232
00:26:57.339 --> 00:26:59.652
I should put a fucking bullet
in your brain right now.

233
00:27:01.758 --> 00:27:04.036
It's not us. Luan.
We don't know where it is.

234
00:27:04.070 --> 00:27:06.314
What do you mean you don't know?
It's gone.

235
00:27:06.348 --> 00:27:08.281
And whoever took your money
took ours as well

236
00:27:08.316 --> 00:27:10.042
so killing me won't change that.

237
00:27:16.980 --> 00:27:19.223
I'm out of fucking time. man.

238
00:27:21.329 --> 00:27:22.848
Mosi won't wait any longer.

239
00:27:24.953 --> 00:27:26.299
You have to help me. Ed.

240
00:27:28.129 --> 00:27:30.027
Luan.

241
00:27:30.062 --> 00:27:32.478
Mosi is your problem.
not ours.

242
00:27:32.512 --> 00:27:34.411
We're honouring your deal
with Finn

243
00:27:34.445 --> 00:27:36.862
not your deal with Mosi.

244
00:27:36.896 --> 00:27:38.933
When we find out who took
our money

245
00:27:38.967 --> 00:27:40.935
we'll both claim back
what's ours.

246
00:27:40.969 --> 00:27:42.246
Until then...

247
00:27:43.144 --> 00:27:44.352
we're all on our own.

248
00:28:15.245 --> 00:28:16.453
So where you taking us?

249
00:28:16.487 --> 00:28:18.869
Somewhere close.
You'll like it.

250
00:28:18.904 --> 00:28:20.699
Yeah. it's really nice.
Get in there...

251
00:28:22.217 --> 00:28:24.530
Wow. cool. a motorbike!

252
00:28:24.564 --> 00:28:26.739
Careful on this. please.

253
00:28:26.774 --> 00:28:28.189
Alright. where we going?

254
00:28:28.223 --> 00:28:30.225
Italy.
Where in Italy?

255
00:28:30.260 --> 00:28:31.433
Uh. Rome.

256
00:28:31.468 --> 00:28:33.746
Rome!

257
00:28:33.781 --> 00:28:34.954
You gonna tell us
when we get there. yeah?

258
00:28:34.989 --> 00:28:35.955
Yep!
OK.

259
00:28:40.028 --> 00:28:41.478
Uh. D-Danny? Danny.

260
00:28:41.512 --> 00:28:42.790
Yeah?
Why don't you go and see

261
00:28:42.824 --> 00:28:44.067
how they're getting on
with our food. yeah?

262
00:28:44.101 --> 00:28:45.516
OK. Mum.
Good boy.

263
00:28:46.483 --> 00:28:47.933
He is a good kid.

264
00:28:51.799 --> 00:28:52.800
Are you alright?

265
00:28:55.872 --> 00:28:57.597
♪ Come on. come on

266
00:28:57.632 --> 00:28:59.116
♪ Cry to me

267
00:29:01.429 --> 00:29:02.810
If this all goes wrong

268
00:29:04.950 --> 00:29:08.125
do you have a fire escape?
Why. what's happened?

269
00:29:08.160 --> 00:29:10.472
Earlier today. I had to help
get rid of a dozen bodies.

270
00:29:10.507 --> 00:29:11.991
Hold on.
were Dad or Alex involved?

271
00:29:12.026 --> 00:29:13.130
No. no. none of us were.

272
00:29:13.165 --> 00:29:15.167
OK.

273
00:29:15.201 --> 00:29:17.894
After Finn's death...
the rivalry...

274
00:29:19.516 --> 00:29:21.138
it's getting worse out there.

275
00:29:22.243 --> 00:29:23.313
What is it?

276
00:29:24.935 --> 00:29:26.143
That can't ever be you.

277
00:29:30.838 --> 00:29:31.839
Well...

278
00:29:33.841 --> 00:29:35.981
I've had a bag packed

279
00:29:36.015 --> 00:29:38.052
ever since it went wrong
with Danny's father.

280
00:29:39.191 --> 00:29:41.158
Passports. cash.
Danny and me. we're gone.

281
00:29:43.643 --> 00:29:45.300
So what about your fire escape?

282
00:29:49.684 --> 00:29:50.892
Would you. um...

283
00:29:54.102 --> 00:29:55.241
would you come with us?

284
00:29:57.554 --> 00:29:59.487
♪ Don't you feel like crying?

285
00:30:00.212 --> 00:30:01.144
♪ Come on...

286
00:30:10.463 --> 00:30:12.396
And even if it does
go all wrong...

287
00:30:17.298 --> 00:30:19.369
...Dad's been worrying me
actually.

288
00:30:19.403 --> 00:30:20.853
He just seems so lost
without Finn--

289
00:30:20.888 --> 00:30:22.303
Hey.

290
00:30:22.337 --> 00:30:23.683
Come away from the window.
What?

291
00:30:23.718 --> 00:30:24.857
Come on.

292
00:30:36.282 --> 00:30:37.007
Hey.

293
00:30:39.147 --> 00:30:41.322
We got nothing from
those two addresses you gave me.

294
00:30:41.356 --> 00:30:42.910
No leads. no clues.

295
00:30:42.944 --> 00:30:44.256
That house was packed
with evidence.

296
00:30:44.290 --> 00:30:46.430
Yeah. if by "packed"
you mean an empty garage

297
00:30:46.465 --> 00:30:48.329
and a hungry eel then yeah.
you were right.

298
00:30:48.363 --> 00:30:51.953
So they were expecting you.
which means you have a link.

299
00:30:51.988 --> 00:30:53.472
Why the fuck have you got
a UC following me?

300
00:30:54.024 --> 00:30:54.922
What?

301
00:30:54.956 --> 00:30:56.233
I should have known
from the beginning

302
00:30:56.268 --> 00:30:57.717
the way he holds his gun

303
00:30:57.752 --> 00:30:59.478
making himself useful
just like me.

304
00:30:59.512 --> 00:31:00.686
Who the fuck put him there?

305
00:31:00.720 --> 00:31:01.756
How do you even know
he's undercover?

306
00:31:01.790 --> 00:31:03.689
I caught him taking pictures
of me and Shannon.

307
00:31:03.723 --> 00:31:04.690
What are you saying?

308
00:31:04.724 --> 00:31:05.864
I'm saying that maybe
he's connected with

309
00:31:05.898 --> 00:31:08.487
whoever's cleaned those houses
before you raided them.

310
00:31:08.521 --> 00:31:09.522
I need him pulled out.

311
00:31:09.557 --> 00:31:11.386
I don't care who he works for.

312
00:31:11.421 --> 00:31:13.388
I cannot operate with him
on my back.

313
00:31:13.423 --> 00:31:15.735
Now. he doesn't know I know
about him yet.

314
00:31:15.770 --> 00:31:17.427
I'll set him up.
you can arrest him

315
00:31:17.461 --> 00:31:18.738
with a bunch of others.
make it look like--

316
00:31:18.773 --> 00:31:20.671
Woah. woah. woah.
Who do you think you are?

317
00:31:20.706 --> 00:31:22.190
That is way too high risk.

318
00:31:22.225 --> 00:31:24.883
Me being under surveillance
is too high risk.

319
00:31:26.298 --> 00:31:27.886
This is how UCs get killed.

320
00:31:29.128 --> 00:31:30.164
Do it.

321
00:31:33.236 --> 00:31:34.375
He's lost his mind.

322
00:31:36.584 --> 00:31:37.999
He takes a bullet
for Sean Wallace

323
00:31:39.345 --> 00:31:40.691
then goes above and beyond

324
00:31:40.726 --> 00:31:42.452
and sleeps with Ed Dumani's
daughter.

325
00:31:44.109 --> 00:31:45.110
Let me level with him.

326
00:31:46.525 --> 00:31:49.114
If I could work with him.
we could do some serious damage.

327
00:31:49.148 --> 00:31:51.979
And what if he chooses
Shannon Dumani and her son

328
00:31:53.394 --> 00:31:54.429
instead of you?

329
00:32:00.332 --> 00:32:01.471
I'm pulling him out.

330
00:32:03.024 --> 00:32:04.957
It might take a little while
to set up.

331
00:32:06.269 --> 00:32:08.340
You'll be briefed
on everything he found out

332
00:32:09.134 --> 00:32:10.204
and I'll keep you in.

333
00:32:12.206 --> 00:32:13.276
If you're up for it?

334
00:32:38.611 --> 00:32:39.992
Colin.

335
00:32:40.372 --> 00:32:41.545
Been a while.

336
00:32:49.622 --> 00:32:51.970
Typical warm Irish welcome.

337
00:32:53.212 --> 00:32:55.594
I always knew
that someday you'd be back.

338
00:32:57.044 --> 00:32:59.322
Despite the fact you set me up
on a one-way ticket.

339
00:32:59.356 --> 00:33:01.013
I didn't set you up.

340
00:33:01.048 --> 00:33:02.635
You didn't try and stop it.

341
00:33:02.670 --> 00:33:04.361
They would've killed us both.

342
00:33:04.396 --> 00:33:05.707
So best to have your
little sister

343
00:33:05.742 --> 00:33:07.399
blown to pieces instead. hmm?

344
00:33:08.124 --> 00:33:09.297
You deserved it.

345
00:33:14.820 --> 00:33:16.442
All dead now. that crowd.

346
00:33:18.548 --> 00:33:21.068
Who killed your man?

347
00:33:21.102 --> 00:33:22.448
I'm still working on that.

348
00:33:23.587 --> 00:33:25.382
And now you want
to give us a yacht?

349
00:33:27.626 --> 00:33:29.145
What would we do with a yacht?

350
00:33:30.111 --> 00:33:31.768
He paid 36 million for it.

351
00:33:33.735 --> 00:33:35.254
Sell it.

352
00:33:35.289 --> 00:33:37.084
You'll get at least
a third of that.

353
00:33:38.188 --> 00:33:39.293
I need your support.

354
00:33:40.087 --> 00:33:41.881
I need your men.

355
00:33:47.680 --> 00:33:49.130
What have you done. Marian?

356
00:33:49.717 --> 00:33:50.821
Oh. shit!

357
00:33:56.862 --> 00:33:58.277
Everything alright. Colin?

358
00:34:03.869 --> 00:34:05.767
Marian fucking Wallace
back from the dead.

359
00:34:21.369 --> 00:34:22.439
You gave us up.

360
00:34:23.164 --> 00:34:24.165
To Asif!

361
00:34:24.579 --> 00:34:25.753
You gave us up!

362
00:34:25.787 --> 00:34:27.134
No. no. no.

363
00:34:27.962 --> 00:34:30.068
Then where was the Wallace
protection. huh?

364
00:34:30.585 --> 00:34:31.621
Where!

365
00:34:34.175 --> 00:34:35.073
Where is it now?

366
00:34:36.729 --> 00:34:38.076
How did you just get to me?

367
00:34:39.836 --> 00:34:41.320
It's fucked. is what it is.

368
00:34:43.598 --> 00:34:44.565
All your people...

369
00:34:45.462 --> 00:34:46.601
I saw them.

370
00:34:51.675 --> 00:34:53.091
I let you down.

371
00:34:54.299 --> 00:34:55.541
And I'm truly sorry.

372
00:34:59.614 --> 00:35:01.754
I can't go against
Asif right now.

373
00:35:02.721 --> 00:35:04.171
There's too much happening.

374
00:35:05.551 --> 00:35:06.587
But I will....

375
00:35:07.864 --> 00:35:10.280
and soon.
I can't wait for "soon".

376
00:35:14.008 --> 00:35:15.492
What do you want to do?

377
00:35:16.390 --> 00:35:18.254
Take what he most cherishes.

378
00:35:28.229 --> 00:35:31.646
Latest poll has you in the lead

379
00:35:31.681 --> 00:35:33.786
Tomorrow you will
sweep to victory.

380
00:35:33.821 --> 00:35:35.788
These scumbag journalists
are calling me

381
00:35:35.823 --> 00:35:37.376
"The Galloping Horse" candidate.

382
00:35:38.239 --> 00:35:39.206
Good slogan.

383
00:35:39.827 --> 00:35:40.897
Backing you to win!

384
00:35:40.931 --> 00:35:42.864
"Horse" is English slang
for heroin.

385
00:35:42.899 --> 00:35:44.280
Ah...
Yeah.

386
00:35:45.557 --> 00:35:46.730
They are linking me

387
00:35:47.766 --> 00:35:49.319
to my drug-dealing father.

388
00:35:49.354 --> 00:35:50.700
An outrageous slur.

389
00:35:52.288 --> 00:35:53.392
I'm not a dealer!

390
00:35:54.290 --> 00:35:55.601
And the attack on Lale?

391
00:35:57.258 --> 00:35:58.639
That was your blunt hand. yes?

392
00:35:59.640 --> 00:36:02.298
That was my strong hand!

393
00:36:57.525 --> 00:36:59.044
You're gonna
wanna see this.

394
00:36:59.078 --> 00:37:00.597
...shocked
by the escalating violence

395
00:37:00.632 --> 00:37:02.012
on the streets of London

396
00:37:02.047 --> 00:37:05.326
as highlighted by the Adige
Investment House massacre.

397
00:37:06.293 --> 00:37:08.053
A police spokesman suggested

398
00:37:08.087 --> 00:37:11.712
a connection to a surge
in violent gangland crime

399
00:37:11.746 --> 00:37:14.749
following the recent shooting
of businessman Finn Wallace

400
00:37:14.784 --> 00:37:16.993
who was patron
of the Wallace Foundation.

401
00:37:17.027 --> 00:37:17.890
His body was--

402
00:37:20.755 --> 00:37:22.585
They attacked one of the oldest
and most trusted

403
00:37:22.619 --> 00:37:24.069
investment houses in the city.

404
00:37:26.796 --> 00:37:28.349
I mean. do you have
any understanding

405
00:37:28.384 --> 00:37:30.420
what that will do
for business confidence?

406
00:37:30.455 --> 00:37:32.836
Yeah. well. maybe killing
Finn Wallace

407
00:37:32.871 --> 00:37:34.493
wasn't such a smart move.

408
00:37:34.528 --> 00:37:35.632
Close of business today

409
00:37:35.667 --> 00:37:37.393
I wanna know
that your son is in control.

410
00:37:38.532 --> 00:37:39.912
Or none of you will be.

411
00:37:59.587 --> 00:38:00.657
Alex?

412
00:38:00.692 --> 00:38:02.314
It has to be Finn.

413
00:38:02.349 --> 00:38:04.040
And it's not just Luan's money
that's gone

414
00:38:04.074 --> 00:38:05.524
there's three more
empty accounts

415
00:38:06.698 --> 00:38:08.113
it's over a billion and a half.

416
00:38:10.771 --> 00:38:12.324
It was Finn Wallace.

417
00:38:12.359 --> 00:38:13.498
No question.

418
00:38:15.776 --> 00:38:18.468
Alex. don't say anything
to anyone until I get there.

419
00:38:23.024 --> 00:38:24.371
You found anything yet?

420
00:38:26.407 --> 00:38:28.133
No. no. No. nothing yet.

421
00:38:32.827 --> 00:38:34.933
I keep coming back
to Luan's photos.

422
00:38:35.692 --> 00:38:36.624
Look.

423
00:38:38.661 --> 00:38:40.007
That's the one
I keep looking at.

424
00:38:43.562 --> 00:38:45.012
That's not who my father was.

425
00:38:49.119 --> 00:38:52.640
Or he had an overwhelming
reason to do what he did.

426
00:38:52.675 --> 00:38:55.609
He was protecting us
from something. something huge.

427
00:38:57.714 --> 00:38:59.958
Dad's big weakness...

428
00:38:59.992 --> 00:39:02.063
he could never confide
in us when things went bad.

429
00:39:04.997 --> 00:39:06.413
You'd tell me. right?

430
00:39:09.588 --> 00:39:10.762
Yeah.

431
00:39:10.796 --> 00:39:11.866
Wallace and Dumani...

432
00:39:12.867 --> 00:39:14.490
no one can fuck us over.

433
00:39:38.237 --> 00:39:40.930
Got a job
for you tomorrow.

434
00:39:40.964 --> 00:39:42.828
We need some guns picking up
from a car park

435
00:39:42.863 --> 00:39:43.864
over in the East End.

436
00:39:44.865 --> 00:39:46.522
Sean's orders?

437
00:39:46.556 --> 00:39:47.902
The fuck are you asking me
questions for?

438
00:39:57.705 --> 00:40:00.156
Mrs Wallace has brought
back her own army with her.

439
00:40:00.190 --> 00:40:01.537
I'll let Sean know.

440
00:40:10.235 --> 00:40:11.754
Welcome back. Mrs Wallace.

441
00:40:11.788 --> 00:40:12.893
Get them food.

442
00:40:19.175 --> 00:40:20.487
Wait in there.

443
00:41:05.739 --> 00:41:06.774
Who the fuck are you?

444
00:41:07.361 --> 00:41:08.776
I work for Mrs Wallace.

445
00:41:12.849 --> 00:41:14.195
Fuck's sake.

446
00:41:14.230 --> 00:41:15.887
Who was that?

447
00:41:15.921 --> 00:41:17.302
Who are those men
in the boardroom?

448
00:41:18.303 --> 00:41:19.580
What the fuck
have you been doing?

449
00:41:23.308 --> 00:41:24.274
Protecting you.

450
00:41:54.822 --> 00:41:56.617
I've always known Ed was lying.

451
00:41:57.584 --> 00:41:58.861
From the very beginning.

452
00:42:00.345 --> 00:42:01.898
Remember.
we only just found out.

453
00:42:03.659 --> 00:42:05.350
Do you think they'll listen
to reason?

454
00:42:06.627 --> 00:42:07.766
Not a chance.

455
00:42:10.666 --> 00:42:12.357
But there's only one way
out of this.

456
00:42:43.733 --> 00:42:44.838
Granny!

457
00:42:52.121 --> 00:42:53.640
I wasn't expecting Danny.

458
00:42:53.674 --> 00:42:55.020
Oh. I thought it was
a "family meeting".

459
00:42:58.886 --> 00:42:59.887
Hey!

460
00:43:06.480 --> 00:43:08.965
Yeah. well.
I couldn't get a sitter.

461
00:43:09.000 --> 00:43:10.933
Danny will be fine
by himself in another room.

462
00:43:14.695 --> 00:43:16.214
Sorry. what is the problem?
What's going on?

463
00:43:26.465 --> 00:43:28.398
Take Danny to the office
and stay with him.

464
00:43:28.433 --> 00:43:30.435
No. I want Elliot in the room.
Just families.

465
00:43:33.818 --> 00:43:34.750
OK.

466
00:43:35.682 --> 00:43:36.717
Let's go. big man.

467
00:43:37.338 --> 00:43:38.305
Hi.

468
00:43:43.241 --> 00:43:44.242
Let's go!

469
00:43:51.007 --> 00:43:52.112
Hi. Dad.
Hey.

470
00:43:52.146 --> 00:43:53.216
Hey.

471
00:43:54.770 --> 00:43:55.633
Hey. babe.

472
00:44:17.206 --> 00:44:18.725
Elliot. come on!

473
00:44:19.173 --> 00:44:20.312
Shh...

474
00:44:23.039 --> 00:44:24.765
You've got some explaining
to do.

475
00:44:26.525 --> 00:44:28.113
How long had you known
about Floriana?

476
00:44:28.148 --> 00:44:30.978
Alexander didn't know anything.
I didn't ask about Alexander.

477
00:44:31.013 --> 00:44:32.531
I'd known
for a couple of months.

478
00:44:32.566 --> 00:44:33.774
You lied to me.

479
00:44:34.499 --> 00:44:36.535
You knew Finn was leaving us?

480
00:44:36.570 --> 00:44:38.745
He only told me
that on the day he was killed.

481
00:44:38.779 --> 00:44:40.436
You've known since then?

482
00:44:40.470 --> 00:44:42.438
I kept it quiet for the sake
of keeping things together.

483
00:44:42.472 --> 00:44:45.372
You kept it quiet
because you were in on it!

484
00:44:45.406 --> 00:44:47.374
You two were always gonna
fucking take over.

485
00:44:47.408 --> 00:44:48.513
That's not true.
Oh. I'm gonna get to you

486
00:44:48.547 --> 00:44:50.308
in a minute.
Sean...

487
00:44:50.342 --> 00:44:52.551
I watched you fall to pieces
after Finn's death.

488
00:44:52.586 --> 00:44:54.519
You needed to believe in him.
we all did.

489
00:44:54.553 --> 00:44:57.142
For the sake of the business.
I kept back what I knew

490
00:44:57.177 --> 00:44:58.937
to keep things straight.

491
00:44:58.972 --> 00:45:01.388
Straight? There's nothing
straight about you.

492
00:45:03.562 --> 00:45:05.564
You've been tagged
since day one

493
00:45:05.599 --> 00:45:07.981
at Jack's flat. exact times.

494
00:45:08.015 --> 00:45:11.294
Arrives 7:40. departs 9:10.
The night you killed him.

495
00:45:13.227 --> 00:45:15.091
Jack knew about Finn and
Floriana leaving together.

496
00:45:16.092 --> 00:45:17.956
Again. for the good
of the family.

497
00:45:17.991 --> 00:45:19.095
Your meetings with Jevan?

498
00:45:19.130 --> 00:45:21.063
Were they for the good
of the family?

499
00:45:21.097 --> 00:45:23.582
Whoever tried to kill me
made sure you two went unharmed.

500
00:45:23.617 --> 00:45:25.239
We didn't know that at the time.
Tsk.

501
00:45:25.274 --> 00:45:26.931
No. no. We've held back
on too much already.

502
00:45:26.965 --> 00:45:28.242
We should've let them in
on things way before

503
00:45:28.277 --> 00:45:30.003
it came to this.
Whoa. whoa. What things?

504
00:45:30.037 --> 00:45:31.314
When we found out who killed
your father

505
00:45:31.349 --> 00:45:33.040
that it was the same people
who tried to kill you.

506
00:45:34.421 --> 00:45:35.767
It was our own investors!

507
00:45:37.355 --> 00:45:40.392
OK. OK.
So. why didn't you tell me?

508
00:45:40.427 --> 00:45:42.222
Because. Sean.
you were out of control.

509
00:45:42.256 --> 00:45:43.602
Out of your control!

510
00:45:58.617 --> 00:46:00.792
What I said at Finn's funeral...

511
00:46:00.827 --> 00:46:03.830
about a good man. those words
were true to me then.

512
00:46:03.864 --> 00:46:05.797
Even though I knew he wanted
a second chance at life.

513
00:46:07.178 --> 00:46:09.939
Some old man's fantasy.
with some pretty girl

514
00:46:09.974 --> 00:46:11.872
but he was still my friend.

515
00:46:11.907 --> 00:46:13.771
Until we found out
what he'd really done.

516
00:46:16.428 --> 00:46:19.569
Look. we both knew
that Finn had Luan kill

517
00:46:19.604 --> 00:46:21.813
this boy along with his family.

518
00:46:21.848 --> 00:46:23.850
What we didn't know until today
was why.

519
00:46:25.437 --> 00:46:27.785
Finn had created a parallel
business for himself.

520
00:46:29.027 --> 00:46:30.580
It wasn't sustainable

521
00:46:30.615 --> 00:46:32.065
he robs new investors

522
00:46:32.099 --> 00:46:34.999
to pay off the old ones
including this boy's father.

523
00:46:35.033 --> 00:46:37.967
He stole from him to pay off
an increasing deficit

524
00:46:38.002 --> 00:46:39.935
but he had no intention
of paying him back

525
00:46:39.969 --> 00:46:41.937
so instead he had him killed.
him and his entire family.

526
00:46:43.179 --> 00:46:45.147
But it still wasn't enough

527
00:46:45.181 --> 00:46:47.977
so he stole the half billion
from Luan and the Nigerians.

528
00:46:48.012 --> 00:46:49.427
I saw that money disappear
in front of my eyes

529
00:46:49.461 --> 00:46:51.049
we both did.

530
00:46:51.084 --> 00:46:52.948
A couple of timed bank transfers

531
00:46:52.982 --> 00:46:55.640
triggered a week after
he would have left.

532
00:46:55.674 --> 00:46:57.400
By the time he planned to vanish
he'd taken

533
00:46:57.435 --> 00:46:58.643
over a billion and a half.

534
